Onboarding & First-Time Experience
Issues:
Onboarding can be skipped — no clear value statement to discourage skipping
Onboarding shows recommended tracks, but unclear how to start them without completing onboarding
Post-onboarding redirect to /app/marketing-track is immediate, but a short success/celebration would help
No preview of the track before committing during onboarding

Missing polish:
No progress indicators or estimated time remaining in onboarding
No way to go back and change previous answers
No confirmation before activating a track (users may want to review)


Dashboard & Empty States
Issues:
Dashboard can be empty if no track is active — the widget shows "No Active Track" but no clear CTA to start one
When tasks are empty, fallback shows all tasks instead of guiding the user to start
Personalization (PersonalizedDashboard) only shows on the dashboard — inconsistent greeting elsewhere

Missing polish:
No "Get Started" guide for new users
No tooltips or help icons for first-time discovery
No sample data or demo mode to illustrate value


Navigation & Information Architecture
Issues:
Sidebar is long — many features visible before users understand them
Mobile sidebar overlays don't clearly communicate the navigation pattern
No breadcrumbs — users may lose context in deep flows
Feature discovery is low — Social Strategy Hub and Social Profile Manager appear conditionally without explanation

Missing polish:
No keyboard shortcuts hint
No search for features or tasks
No recent activity or "last viewed" shortcuts


Marketing Track Experience
Issues:
Track selection happens in onboarding, but unclear how to switch tracks later
If no track is active, the marketing track page shows an error instead of a track selector
Week progression is unclear — what unlocks next week? How do you advance?
Task descriptions are hidden in modals — requires clicks to understand what to do

Missing polish:
No progress celebration (confetti exists but minimal use)
No preview of upcoming weeks
No way to "catch up" if behind


Error Handling & User Feedback
Issues:
Error messages are technical (e.g., "Track data loaded but not active") instead of user-friendly
API failures show generic errors — no actionable recovery steps
Loading states are inconsistent — some pages show spinners, others show skeletons
No offline indication — what happens if the network fails mid-action?

Missing polish:
No retry mechanisms for failed requests
No optimistic UI updates (tasks should feel instant)
No clear success feedback for many actions


Subscription & Access Flow
Issues:
Paywall appears abruptly — no grace period or "days remaining" banner beforehand
Subscription page shows all plans but doesn't highlight what you're missing
Trial expiration isn't communicated proactively — only at access denial
No way to see usage/engagement before trial ends

Missing polish:
No upgrade prompts based on feature usage
No preview of premium features for trial users
Cancel flow is hidden in subscription management


Task Management
Issues:
Task creation has a 500ms debounce — may feel unresponsive
No task templates or quick-add options
No bulk actions (complete multiple, delete multiple)
No task prioritization or due date sorting

Missing polish:
No keyboard shortcuts for task operations
No drag-and-drop reordering
No task dependencies or subtasks


AI Features
Issues:
AI Assistant is separate from the context where you're working — FloatingAssistant is separate from page context
No conversation history persistence — conversations disappear on refresh
Error states are generic — "having trouble connecting" doesn't suggest what to do
No examples or prompts to get started

Missing polish:
No rate limit warnings
No cost indication for AI usage
No way to save favorite prompts


Mobile Experience
Issues:
Mobile sidebar requires multiple taps — no quick access to common features
Forms (onboarding, profile) have long scrolls on mobile — no step indicators
Tables/grids may not be optimized for small screens
Touch targets may be too small in some areas

Missing polish:
No mobile-specific gestures (swipe to complete tasks)
No bottom navigation bar for quick access
No mobile app-like experience


Profile & Settings
Issues:
Profile has many tabs but unclear what's required vs. optional
Branding settings don't preview how they'll look
No account deletion or data export
Email preferences are separate from notification preferences — could be confusing

Missing polish:
No profile completion indicator
No way to test notifications
No change history or undo for settings


Critical Missing Features
Search — no way to find tasks, lessons, or content
Export — no way to export tasks, progress, or data
Integrations — no calendar sync, Slack, or other tools
Analytics — no insights into usage, completion rates, or trends
Sharing — no way to share progress or collaborate
Offline mode — no offline capability


Small Details That Add Up
No "What's New" or changelog
No help documentation or tutorials in-app
No keyboard navigation patterns (Tab order, Enter to submit)
No dark/light mode toggle (dark only)
No print-friendly views for tasks/lessons
No undo for destructive actions
No confirmation dialogs for critical actions (deleting, canceling subscription)
No empty state illustrations (just text)


